At last, Ld. Appellate Court concluded that for the purpose of granting interim injunction under Order 39 Rule 1 & 2 Cpc, there is need to make out a case of granting of temporary injunction, same being covered with three basic principles, which are:-
(i) Prima facie case;
(ii) Balance of convenience; and
(iii) Irreparable loss or injury;
Cr-5837-2023 (O&M) -7- Learned Appellate Court found that case of plaintiff is not meeting out with the settled parameters.

For the said purpose, this Court is again guided with the observations made by their Lordships in the case of Robust Hotels Pvt. Ltd.'s case (supra), wherein, it is observed that the bar of jurisdiction of Civil Court has to co- relate to the two conditions i.e.;
"(i) Any suit or proceedings in respect of any matter, in which the Debts Recovery Tribunal or Appellate Tribunal is empowered by or under this Act to determine."
(ii) Further, no injunction shall be granted by any Court or other authority in respect of any action taken or to be taken in pursuance of any power conferred by or under this Act or under the Recovery of Debts Due to Banks and Financial Institutions Act, 1993".
